     <header> 
      <a href="https://www.ipetitions.com/my/petitions/553680" id="edit-petition-url" style="display: none" rel="nofollow" class="editpetition small-button white right single">Edit Petition</a> 
      <h1 id="petition_title">Tell Hilton Hotels to Go 100% Shark Fin Free</h1> 
     </header> 
     <div class="meta"> 
     </div> 
     <span class="expand"><a id="toggle" class="" href="#"><b></b></a></span> 
     <div class="petition"> 
      <p></p>
      <p><br><br>In the west you won’t find shark fin soup on Hilton Hotels’ restaurant menus. However their Vice President of Corporate Responsibility has admitted that it is being sold to customers who request it at their Hotels in the Far East. Hilton Hotels recognise that there is a serious issue with shark fin soup, which is why they no longer publish it on their menus. But they should take one final step and ban it completely from their restaurants.<br><br><b>Please sign this petition and tell Hilton Hotels that you want them to go 100% shark fin free.</b><br><br>More information at <b>Stop Shark Finning</b>.<br></p>
      <p></p> 
      <h3>Sponsor</h3>
      <div>
       <p>Stop Shark Finning</p>
      </div> 
      <h3>Links</h3>
      <div>
       <p>More information at the <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="Stop shark finning" href="http://stopsharkfinning.net/">Stop Shark Finning</a> website.<br><br><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="Ask Hilton Hotels to ban shark fin from all their restaurants." href="http://stopsharkfinning.posterous.com/gtrgr">Article published in July 2012</a>.<br><br><br></p>
      </div> 
     </div> 
